Arsenal, on transfer deadline day (Monday), announced that Auston Trusty has joined the club from Colorado Rapids. Arsenal also confirmed that Tim Akinola has left Emirates to join Scottish Premiership side Dundee United on loan for the rest of the season. The Gunners disclosed this in a separate statement via their website. The statement read, “Defender Auston Trusty has joined the club in a permanent transfer from Colorado Rapids but will remain with the MLS side on loan. “The USA under-20 international joined Colorado Rapids from Philadelphia Union in November 2019. “Trusty, 23, will stay with the Colorado Rapids until at least the end of the Premier League season in May.” It added, “Young midfielder Tim Akinola has joined Scottish Premiership side Dundee United on loan for the remainder of the 2021/22 season. “The 20-year-old joined us from Huddersfield Town in summer 2020 and went on to make 21 Premier League 2 appearances last season.”